      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 466: This path reads loadedHistory_.quickAccess and mutates sharedMsg-\u003epluginData without holding loadedHistory_.mutex, while other new methods clear and update the same map under that mutex. That introduces a data race and can corrupt message state when history loading, plugin callbacks, or cache clearing happen concurrently. Copy the message under the lock, run plugin code outside the lock, then reacquire the lock to publish the result if the message still exists.\n```suggestion\nlibjami::SwarmMessage msgCopy;\n{\n    std::lock_guard lk(loadedHistory_.mutex);\n    auto it \u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.find(idIt-\u003esecond);\n    if (it \u003d\u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.end())\n        return;\n    msgCopy \u003d *it-\u003esecond;\n}\nstd::vector single {msgCopy};\npluginChatManager.transformSwarmMessages(single, accountId_, convId);\nconst auto bodyOverwriteIt \u003d single[0].pluginData.find(\"bodyOverwrite\");\nif (bodyOverwriteIt !\u003d single[0].pluginData.end()) {\n    libjami::SwarmMessage updated;\n    {\n        std::lock_guard lk(loadedHistory_.mutex);\n        auto it \u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.find(idIt-\u003esecond);\n        if (it \u003d\u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.end())\n            return;\n        it-\u003esecond-\u003epluginData[\"bodyOverwrite\"] \u003d bodyOverwriteIt-\u003esecond;\n        updated \u003d *it-\u003esecond;\n    }\n    emitSignal\u003clibjami::ConversationSignal::SwarmMessageUpdated\u003e(accountId_, convId, updated);\n}\n```",
