      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 266: transformSwarmMessages currently invokes every loaded ChatHandler, regardless of whether that handler is enabled for the {accountId, conversationId}. This exposes loaded conversation history to disabled plugins and lets them alter pluginData for conversations they are not attached to. Reuse the same allow/deny and toggled checks used by publishMessage before calling a handler.\n```suggestion\nstd::pair\u003cstd::string, std::string\u003e key(accountId, conversationId);\nconst auto toggledIt \u003d chatHandlerToggled_.find(key);\nconst auto allowIt \u003d allowDenyList_.find(key);\nfor (auto\u0026 handler : chatHandlers_) {\n    const auto handlerName \u003d handler-\u003egetChatHandlerDetails().at(\"name\");\n    const auto handlerPtr \u003d reinterpret_cast\u003cuintptr_t\u003e(handler.get());\n    const bool explicitlyEnabled \u003d allowIt !\u003d allowDenyList_.end()\n        \u0026\u0026 allowIt-\u003esecond.contains(handlerName)\n        \u0026\u0026 allowIt-\u003esecond.at(handlerName);\n    const bool toggled \u003d toggledIt !\u003d chatHandlerToggled_.end()\n        \u0026\u0026 toggledIt-\u003esecond.contains(handlerPtr);\n    if (explicitlyEnabled || toggled)\n        handler-\u003etransformSwarmMessages(messages, accountId, conversationId);\n}\n```",
